typedef unsigned int IALG_Cmd

Algorithm specific command.

Remarks:
This command is used in conjunction with IALG_Status to get and set algorithm specific attributes via the algControl() method.

Definition at line 47 of file ialg.h.

enum IALG_MemSpace

Defined memory spaces.

Enumerator:
IALG_EPROG  External program memory
IALG_IPROG  Internal program memory
IALG_ESDATA  Off-chip data memory (accessed sequentially)
IALG_EXTERNAL  Off-chip data memory (accessed randomly)
IALG_DARAM0  Dual access on-chip data memory
IALG_DARAM1  Block 1, if independant blocks required
IALG_SARAM  Single access on-chip data memory
IALG_SARAM0  Block 0, equivalent to IALG_SARAM
IALG_SARAM1  Block 1, if independant blocks required
IALG_DARAM2  Block 2, if a 3rd independent block required
IALG_SARAM2  Block 2, if a 3rd independent block required
